{
  "texts": [
    "To facilitate fair comparison and follow-up research, we provide additional results for our proposed method at various SNR levels.",
    "The experiments were conducted at SNR levels of -15, -10, -5, 0, 5, 10, and 15 dB, following previous works.",
    "Table 8 illustrates the WERs at each SNR level.",
    "Across the different SNR levels, the proposed method outperforms the previous approach (Cheng et al., 2023a).",
    "Specifically, performance at 10dB to 15dB is comparable to that observed in a clean environment, while substantial improvements are evident between -10dB and 0dB."
  ]
}